courses.description: Basic principles of partnership accounting and the accrual basis of accounting.

Prerequisite: ACCT 102 or equivalent. Principles and concepts of the accounting cycle. Internal controls as needed for special journals, cash management, and inventories are presented along with an understanding of financial statements.
Prerequisite: ACCT 200. Accounting for partnerships and corporations with special emphasis on accounting procedures for the assets and liabilities commonly found in business.
Prerequisite: ACCT 201. Application of accounting concepts and techniques to managerial problems of planning, control, decision making.
Prerequisite: Sophomore standing. Consideration of the nature, formation, and application of law in general; emphasis on public law and regulation of business.
This is an introductory course dealing with the economic importance of the agribusiness community and the potential for employment with the agribusiness industry.
An introduction to the preparation of farm records and financial statements for use in business analysis.
Comparison of scientific and holistic thought models as applied to personal, organizational, and biological problem solving and goal setting.
Corequisite: AGEC 240. Applications of the holistic model to biological, financial, and land planning.
Economic and managerial concepts related to farm or agribusiness production process, development of cost data, enterprise analysis, organization and management of production inputs.
